        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 10 at 1:01PM MDT by NWS Pueblo CO</headline>
        <description>At 101 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Spanish Peaks, or 24 miles northwest of Trinidad, moving northeast at
15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Aguilar and Gulnare.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
